Code is available on GitHub. Check the dev branch for most the recent changes.

The limelight feed is really slow in Elastic, like 1fps or just frozen. Going to the limelight ip directly on chrome has the feed at normal fps and Shuffleboard also has a normal speed feed.

We load in tomorrow and our team doesn’t have a programming mentor, so help would be appreciated. I’m the only programmer and any advice will help.

Which version of Elastic are you running? There was an issue with Camera Streams that was fixed earlier in the season. If you’re using the WPILib version of Elastic, it won’t automatically check for updates, you’ll have to either install the newest release of WPILib, or install Elastic from the link on Elastic’s github release page (which you can find in the thread linked below)

Elastic 2025: A Lot of Little Things

Camera Stream Speed Fix

A critical issue was fixed where not all images were properly processed in an image stream, leading to low FPS, miscalculated bandwidth, and invalid images/glitch effects.

Camera stream performance should significantly improve.

Let me know if this works, it sounds like the issue that was fixed in a post-kickoff update

Good luck at the competition!
